Mandaviya justified allowing personal coaches for athletes' mental well-being. He highlighted the government's Rs 470 crore investment in 16 disciplines and discussed future goals, including making India a sporting powerhouse. Mandaviya emphasized the importance of government support and the positive impact on athletes' performance.

description: It's been a week since Team India all-rounder Hardik Pandya and Natasa Stankovic announced their separation. Stankovic shared joyful images on Instagram of herself and their son Agastya at a dinosaur-themed park in Serbia. Pandya commented with supportive emojis. The couple, married since 2020 and separated in July 2024, emphasized their decision was mutual. Despite online misogyny faced by Stankovic, Pandya's positive comments garnered significant attention, with fans expressing hope for their reconciliation.

Israeli and American flags could be seen in the background.

As part of the charge sheet submitted by the Mumbai Police to a court regarding the incident, the actor revealed that the gang's motive behind the attack was to kill him and his family members.

description: The Karnataka BJP announced on Wednesday a plan to hold a "day and night" protest in the state assembly and council. This move comes in response to allegations that discussions related to the Muda "scam," involving chief minister Siddaramaiah's wife, were discouraged in the House. BJP accused the assembly speaker of favouring the ruling Congress during the state House proceedings. They also criticised chief minister Siddaramaiah, stating that Karnataka is being run by a "government of cowards."

description: Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman has unveiled the Budget for 2024, and during her speech, she announced that the government has allocated Rs 1.48 lakh crore for education, employment, and skilling. The incident occurred during an event graced by the presence of West Bengal's chief minister, Mamata Banerjee. The Information and Cultural Affairs Department had organized the program to honor the memory of the legendary actor Uttam Kumar on the occasion of his 44th death anniversary.

description: Alphabet's Q2 2024 revenue hit $85 billion, a 14% rise year-over-year. Google Cloud topped $10 billion for the first time. The police acted after receiving a complaint on social media about the incident. Aditya, in his Spider-Man costume, and Gaurav were soon identified and apprehended by the authorities.

description: The Bihar assembly passed the Bihar Public Examinations (PE) (Prevention of Unfair Means) Bill, 2024, by voice vote on Wednesday to reinforce measures against examination irregularities. This move aims to address the issue of paper leaks and other malpractices that have previously resulted in the cancellation of several crucial examinations. The bill stipulates severe penalties for those involved in such malpractices, including a prison term of three to five years and a fine of Rs 10 lakh.
title: Bihar passes anti-paper leak bill to enforce measures against malpractices

description: Apple launched the 'Apple Watch For Your Kids' feature in India, allowing parents to set up an Apple Watch for their children without an iPhone. It supports models from Apple Watch Series 4 and SE with cellular. The feature includes communication, safety, and activity tracking, all manageable through the parent's iPhone. A separate cellular plan is required. Available via Jio.

description: A 26-year-old youth, Nilesh Rai, lost his life in a tragic electrocution incident in Patel Nagar. Rai, a civil services exam aspirant, was electrocuted when he grabbed an iron gate near a waterlogged area. Despite rescue attempts, Rai's body remained stuck to the gate due to entangled threads. Authorities have registered a case of negligence and obstruction in public way. Investigations are ongoing, with forensic teams examining the scene. The electricity distributor attributed the incident to current leakage from damaged motor wiring.

description: The Delhi High Court has transferred the investigation of a 23-year-old man's death during communal riots to the CBI, terming it a 'hate crime'. The court criticized the police for alleged religious bigotry and lack of accountability. With perpetrators still unidentified and concerns over police negligence, the court's decision aims to ensure a fair and credible investigation process. The case underscores the importance of upholding human rights and addressing issues of mob vigilantism, even when involving law enforcement officials.
